<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-07-08T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-07-08T00:00:00-05:00" n="939" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d939">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">811.111 Habicht, Hermann: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Steinhardt</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Moscow</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-07-08">July 8,
                                1941</date>.<lb/>[Received July 8—6:21 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>1322. As Soviet authorities have finally agreed to issue exit visas to
                            Mrs. Hermann Habicht and son and to Mrs. Robert Magidoff, please
                            authorize immediate issuance immigration visas and allot one
                            non-preference Soviet Union quota number for issuance to minor son of
                            Mrs. Habicht.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Steinhardt</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>